      },
      "date": "2013-06-07 01:00:09.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nFan Yong, this is fairly typical for static code analysis tools.  As you write, since this is the initialization phase, it is not harmful to hold the lock.  The only danger in such cases is if the lock is not yet initialized at this part of the code, but that doesn't seem to be a problem here.\n\nSebastien, unfortunately a build bug was landed to the master branch caused by the conflict of two patches that built OK separately.  Please rebase your patches once http://review.whamcloud.com/6565 has landed (hopefully by tomorrow), or rebase them to commit 614665d3201b4de385e3fab6d7d99e1468fde0d4 (just before the broken patch landed).",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
